Quotes.md
“Causality is structure enforced by ignorance.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“Our scientific concepts do not describe nature—they describe our relationship to nature.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“In the beginning was the probability wave.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“Probability replaces certainty in the smallest scales.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“Quantum theory does not describe reality itself, but what we can say about reality.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“Uncertainty is not a mistake—it is a fundamental feature.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“Not only is the universe stranger than we think, it is stranger than we can think.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“In the strict formulation of the law of causality... it is not the consequence that is uncertain, but the cause.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“Nature is made in such a way as to be able to be understood.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“Every experiment destroys some of the knowledge of the system which was obtained by previous experiments.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“The more precisely the position is determined, the less precisely the momentum is known.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“What we observe is not nature itself, but nature exposed to our method of questioning.” – Werner Heisenberg.md
“The measure of information is independent of the language used to encode it.” – Claude Shannon.md
“True secrecy systems are structurally identical to noise.” – Claude Shannon.md
“Capacity is not a function of power. It is a function of distinction.” – Claude Shannon.md
“Redundancy determines resilience.” – Claude Shannon.md
“The concept of entropy applies to any system where probability governs structure.” – Claude Shannon.md
“It is not the message, but the structure of transmission that defines the channel.” – Claude Shannon.md
“Noise is that which disrupts distinction.” – Claude Shannon.md
“The significant aspect is not the actual content, but the selection of possibilities.” – Claude Shannon.md
“We are not concerned with semantics.” – Claude Shannon.md
“A mathematical theory of communication... should serve as a broad framework.” – Claude Shannon.md
“The system must be considered as a whole, not merely in its parts.” – Claude Shannon.md
“Any difference that makes a difference can be a signal.” – Claude Shannon.md
